value.value: Larval neuron that has its soma located ventrally in an abdominal neuromere and expresses allatostatin A and diuretic hormone 31 (Park et al., 2008).

definition.value: Unclear from Park et al. (2008) which segments this is found in, diagram is based on A1.

value.value: Larval neuron that has its soma located dorsolaterally in an abdominal neuromere and expresses allatostatin A (Park et al., 2008).

definition.value: Unclear from Park et al. (2008) which segments this is found in, diagram is based on A8. Not reported as expressing Dh31.

value.value: Neuron that has its soma in the dorsal part of an abdominal neuromere and expresses the neuropeptide Nplp1 (Park et al., 2008).

label.value: larval Drosulfakinin neuron of medial protocerebrum

value.value: Larval Drosulfakinin neuron with its soma in the medial protocerebrum (Park et al., 2008). There are two of these cell per hemisphere and they also express Allatostatin C (Park et al., 2008).

label.value: larval sNPF/Ms cell of medial protocerebrum

value.value: Neuron of the larval medial protocerebrum that expresses dromyosuppressin (DMS) and short neuropeptide F (sNPF) (Park et al., 2008). There are two of these cells per hemisphere (Park et al., 2008).
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that expresses NPF (FBgn0027109).
Larval neuron that has its soma located in then ventral posterior brain and expresses allatostatin A (Park et al., 2008).

Immature tendon cell of the embryo (Volk, 1999). It arises from the ectoderm (Volk, 1999). It produces signals that attract a developing muscle towards the attachment site (Schweitzer et al., 2010). Only a subset of these, which become bound to a myotube, develop into mature tendon cells (Volk, 1999), and the others dedifferentiate (Soler et al., 2016).

definition.value: Can be identified based on expression of Stripe (Volk et al., 1999).

value.value: Tendon cell of an adult leg muscle. It develops from the leg disc epithelium (Soler et al., 2016).
Tendon cell of a flight muscle. It develops from the wing disc epithelium (Soler et al., 2016).

Epithelial cell that is in the process of becoming an adult tendon cell (Soler et al., 2010). Many of these cells are closely associated with myoblasts and undergo changes in gene expression and morphology in the late larva and pupa (Soler et al., 2010).
Immature form of a distal medullary amacrine neuron (Konstantinides et al., 2022).
Immature form of a lobula columnar neuron (Konstantinides et al., 2022).
Immature form of a transmedullary neuron (Konstantinides et al., 2022).

label.value: immature optic lobe centrifugal columnar neuron

value.value: Immature form of a centrifugal columnar neuron (Konstantinides et al., 2022).

Structure of the adult mushroom body calyx formed by one or more Kenyon cell dendritic claws wrapping around a projection neuron axonal bouton (Leiss et al., 2009). Other extrinsic neurons may also contribute to the structure, but it is not wrapped by glial processes (Leiss et al., 2009). There are around 1500 microglomeruli per calyx (Leiss et al., 2009).

Oviposition descending neuron that curves laterally into both sides of the posterior abdominal neuromere (Sturner et al., 2024). In the brain, it bifurcates near the midline forming a dorsal projection that arborizes in the superior medial protocerebrum, as well as a ventral descending branch, similar to oviDNb (Sturner et al., 2024). There are two of these cells per hemisphere (Sturner et al., 2024).

Secondary neuron that will develop into an adult motor neuron, but is still in an immature state (Nguyen et al., 2024). These neurons remain relatively metabolically and functionally inactive during the larval stage (Nguyen et al., 2024).
Motor neuron born during the larval stage. These neurons function as part of the adult nervous system (Nguyen et al., 2024).

label.value: adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus

value.value: Tract that contains the axons of a large number of descending neurons that project to the tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). The majority of its neurons bend ventrally upon entering the VNC, with a smaller number following the dorsal surface of the VNC and joining the ventral neurons more posteriorly (Namiki et al., 2018).

definition.value: Cheong et al. (2024) say the main ventral tract does not overlap with DMT from Court et al. (2020) - FBrf0246815.

label.value: adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus I

value.value: Tract that forms part of the adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus and contains descending neurons that bend ventrally upon entering the VNC (Namiki et al., 2018; Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Cheong et al. (2024) say this tract does not overlap with DMT from Court et al. (2020) - FBrf0246815.

label.value: adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus II

value.value: Tract that forms part of the adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus (MTD) and contains descending neurons that follow the dorsal surface of the VNC before rejoining the remainder of the MTD (Namiki et al., 2018; Cheong et al., 2024).
Tract of the ventral nerve cord with a curved morphology and a ventrolateral position (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Found in MANC and FANC (Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus III

value.value: Tract that forms part of the adult median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus and contains axons that take a relatively lateral route (Cheong et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

definition.value: Found in MANC and FANC (Sturner et al., 2024).

value.value: Intrinsic neuron of the medulla with its main arbors in the central (M6/M7) layers (Nern et al., 2024).

Larval neuron with its cell body and dendritic arbors in the subesophageal ganglion (Zhu et al., 2024). Its axon follows the midline along most of the length of the ventral nerve cord, innervating medial regions bilaterally (Zhu et al., 2024). There is one of these cells on each side (Zhu et al., 2024). It provides inhibitory GABAergic input to nociceptive rolling circuits (Zhu et al., 2024).

Embryonic cardioblast that will become an adult ostial cell (Molina and Cripps, 2001). They can be recognized by their expression of seven up, and in the assembled dorsal vessel of the late embryo, there are two in each of hemisegments A1-A4 (Molina and Cripps, 2001; Lehmacher et al., 2012; Chen et al., 2016). It does not form an ostium in the larva, but differentiates into an adult ostial cell during pupal development (Molina and Cripps, 2001; Lehmacher et al., 2012).

Embryonic cardioblast that will become an ostial cell (Molina and Cripps, 2001). There are two of these cells in each of hemisegments A1-A7, found near the posterior segment boundary, and they can be recognized by their expression of seven up (Molina and Cripps, 2001; Lehmacher et al., 2012; Chen et al., 2016).
An elongating spermatid, 200-500 micrometers in length and in which nuclear shaping has begun. The two parts of the mitochondrial derivative become unequal in size.
A nearly fully elongated spermatid bigger than 1.2 mm length, with a needle-shaped nucleus.
An elongating spermatid 0.8-1.2 mm in length, with a nucleus resembling a canoe.
A cyst cell which is part of a spermatocyte cyst.
A cyst cell which is part of a polar spermatocyte cyst.
A cyst cell which is part of an apolar spermatocyte cyst.
A cyst cell which is part of a mature spermatocyte cyst.
Cyst cell of a spermatid cyst.
The member of a cyst cell pair that envelopes the head of a developing spermatid.

The member of a cyst cell pair that envelopes the tail of a developing spermatid. During spermatid elongation, tail cyst cells become very long and thin as they extend to cover the growing sperm flagellum.
Cell that develops into or is itself a spermatozoon.
Cell that develops into or is itself an egg.

definition.value: Can be identified by expression of vasa (Rust et al., 2020).

value.value: A columnar epithelium inside the testis basal lamina in the terminal (basal) 10% of the testis.

Epithelial cell of the terminal epithelium of the testis. These cells engulf the head cyst cell of a spermatid cyst during coiling, so anchoring the head of the coiling spermatid. These cells also phagocytose the waste bags and cyst cells left over at the end of spermatogenesis.
Primary spermatocyte during meiosis I (GO:0007127).

label.value: primary spermatocyte in meiotic prophase I

value.value: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic prophase I (GO:0007128).

definition.value: Make into XP once OBO:rel 'during' is legal.

label.value: primary spermatocyte in meiotic metaphase I

value.value: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic metaphase I (GO:0007132). The chromatin is highly condensed, the parafusorial or paranuclear membranes (three to five layers of double membranes) encircle the nucleus and the astral membranes (stack of approximately 13 umbrella-shaped layers, each with a central hole) cup each pole of the spindle-shaped nucleus. The mitochondria are clustered around the equator of the spindle region and oriented parallel to the long axis of the cell.

definition.value: Make into XP once OBO:rel 'during' is legal.

label.value: primary spermatocyte in meiotic telophase I

value.value: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic telophase 1 (GO:0007134). In early telophase the daughter nucleus forms within the karyoplasm and the remnants of karyoplasmic structures. At late telophase, two nuclear membranes have formed around the nucleus of the future secondary spermatocyte, the parafusorial or paranuclear membranes (three to five layers of double membranes) have dissolved and the cell wall has thickened at the site of maximal invagination.
